-- Deutsche put EBRD's 2.5 pct stake in Enea for sale -sources
-- By Adrian Krajewski
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 06:41AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, April 10 (Reuters) - Deutsche Bank is selling European Bank for Reconstruction and Development's [EBRD.UL] 2.5 percent stake in Polish utility Enea <ENAE.WA>, with buyer interest hovering around 14.75 zlotys ($4.89) per share, three market sources told Reuters on Thursday.

According to sources, 11 million Enea shares have been put on the block, valuing the stake at 162.3 million zlotys. Enea trades at 15.07 zlotys per share, or 3.6-percent lower in Thursday trade on the Warsaw bourse.